name: Create GitHub Repository
summary: Create a new GitHub repository using gh CLI and push code

steps.text: Open terminal application and navigate to project directory
steps.action: Launch terminal and execute cd command

steps.text: Create GitHub repository using CLI with 'gh repo create myproject --public'
Add remote origin URL to local git repository
steps.action: Execute git remote add origin command

steps.text: Push local changes to GitHub main branch
steps.action: Execute git push -u origin main command
